name: TKE-Djibouti Power Light
product_desc:
The electricity produced will generate 50% return on investment beginning in year 2.

This project will provide the Republic of Djibouti with an immediate answer to their electric needs, and kickstart them to becoming 100% energy independent through renewable energy.

The project development is 90% completed with all licensing, agreements, land purchase, and studies completed.  

Once in operation the project with provide up to 52 mega-watts of electricity to several major end users through the use of conventional power generation, and renewable energy (PV Solar).  This will be done with the construction of a hybrid micro-grid that will be located in a secure location next to the US military base (Camp Lemonier).

The pricing of the electricity for the US military is $100/Megawatt less than what they are currently paying.  They will realize an immediate $16,000,000/year savings with us.  

There is no competition in this market--none.
markets: Governments, Commercial Solar, Electrical Distribution, DOD/Military
